caption: Love this spot. Simple and delicious, great location
Must stop for cocktails and food!
Best hot pressed Cubans in the city !
Would attention again.
Not the spot for take out! Arroz con Pollo had so little flavor I used the chicken for caesar salad instead.

Manolito fills a Cuban void in a city otherwise filled with Cajun and Creole cuisine. The food menu is filled with Cuban staples, and the drink menu is packed with Caribbean and Cuban favorites. While everything is good, nothing struck me as great. If you're looking for a po boy alternate or hangover helper this is perfect.

Liked it so much I went there twice on my vacation to New Orleans. The Chickepea salad, arepas and cafe Cubano were wonderful. My husband said their mojito was the best he's ever had. EDIT: I just went back again. My original review is from July 2018. This place is AMAZING. I had two Cafe de Coco and I can't wait to go back again. Everyone working there is so nice. The service was some of the best I have ever had.

Drinks here were great. Really wished they had inside sitting available so we could have enjoyed their food too but it was a rainy night. We'll definitely be stopping by again in our next trip to New Orleans.
Loved the Daiquiris!
Can’t recommend the jazz daiquiri enough. It’s a daiquiri that’s packed with flavor and not sugar! It was smaller than I expected, but that’s not going to stop me from trying more on the menu

Either be open or don't be.  U will serve me a drink and food but send me to a homeless bathroom two blocks away with no soap or running water.  Then you have me come back and sit on your chairs.  I'd rather not patronize your business.   That's sad...I wanted to spend money and tip more...and here we are.   Ur closing back down completely in two days .
Brilliant cocktails

Didn't know this place existed. If you blink you'll miss it but I'm really glad we didn't miss it because that cuban was so good. We weren't that hungry at first, so me and my boyfriend ordered one cuban sandwich to split and after we ate it, we wanted more. The cuban is different than any other cuban we've tasted before, but man was it good. Try this place out!
These guys are holding it down across from the skate shop so hard. If you’re looking for the best piná colada then look no further. Great small plates and even great service!!!
10/10 would reccommend this place to anyone. The tastys cocktails ever!!
One of the best places we’ve eaten in New Orleans. Cocktails were very good, and the food was even better. Highly recommend the arepas and the black bean hummus.
Delicious cocktails, friendly staff, fun ambiance. Will be back!
I didn't catch his name but the host/server was very kind and volunteered advice on the city that I was happy to have.
Awesome little spot that you don't want to miss! Great food. Excellent service. Don't blink as you could miss it.
(Translated by Google) Long live Cuba!  (Original) Viva la Cuba!
A bit overpriced. Not the type of Cuban food I was expecting.
Delicious cuban food. You should go. We didn't get a chance to try the cocktails but we will be back!

Cozy, eclectic spot for a drink and a quick bite. Try the hummus for sure, you won't be disappointed! As far as hummus goes, it's nothing like I was expecting! Drink-wise, the mint daquiri is a great choice too!
Small place, but friendly staff. It does kinda feel like a hole in the wall bar in cuba. A good change of pace when you've had enough of the gumbo and cajun stuff.
Charming. Fabulous ceviche and a great selection of sipping rums.
Great little place with fun Cuban inspired drinks.   It’s small and warm inside but the employees are very friendly and the drinks are delicious.
The best daquiri ever.I had a banana daquiri made by Ms.Lilly Maher and it was delicious.Lilly's showmanship and skill are incredible.
Stellar service and strong libations. The blended drinks were excellent and they've got a lot to choose from!
Great drinks

Always fabulous! Well made cocktails you won't find everywhere. On a warm day get a frozen mint daquiri to go. You will enjoy strolling through the Quarter even more while sipping on a frozen mint daquiri from Manolito.

Truly a hidden gem, I guess 99% of people simply walk by this little restaurant and bar. We discovered it by accident too. Sadly we already had dinner just before so I couldn't try the food. However, probably the best Daiquiri I ever had and I really recommend you to try the banana one. Sounds weird? Yes, but delicious! The place is co-owned by most of the staff, or all if I understood that right. That gives the place familiar, relaxed flair and everyone it's super friendly. I'll be back when I'm again in New Orleans.

We walked in on a whim and were absolutely blown away by the quality of the food, drinks, and service! The restaurant itself is quite small but they do a great job of developing a wonderful ambiance. We got the hummus, croquetas, chickpeas, arepas, and banana fritters. Everything was SO good, and our waitress Josephine was amazing, she went out of her way to make sure we enjoyed everything, and gave us recommendations for things to do in the city after we left!
10/10 great drinks great food. Josephine is a doll!

Stepping in to Manolito's is like stepping into a cafe along the main drag in Havana. The staff is amazingly friendly and SUPER helpful when you are looking for local spots to eat and drink that are off the beaten path but still in the French Quarter.  Our server Cas treated us like family and the bartender mixed up some wicked great cocktails for us (their Martini is one of the best I've ever had).  Every place we've been to in New Orleans since asking for recommendations from the staff here has been an absolute knock out. These folks go above and beyond!
Fabulous cocktails. Fantastic staff. Highly recommend. Local and non-touristy space.
i don’t know much about cuban food. but i know good food. and this place was damn good. mojitos paired perfectly.
Authentic and cozy. Delicious food and drinks, good people.
I love Manolito
One of the best cubins sammies ever

Fantastic food and atmosphere, the kitchen had a problem where they couldn't serve a few items today,b that didn't impact the taste of anything! I got the Ropa Vieja and some Arepas, which were both amazing and filled me up. My friend recommended this place to me for their mojitos and I have to agree with her that it was the best mojito I've ever had!!
Little known new Cuban restaurant.  GREAT FOOD!
It's a good place. But if you have a cuban stomach portions are too small. Taste amazing. But be prepare for some spicy taste. Helloooo you are in New Orleans. 5 stars service.

Seriously,  one of the best kept secrets in the quarter. With an intimate setting, awesome staff, perfect, handmade cocktails, and legit Cuban food (best Cuban sandwich in the quarter), this place is my go to joint in new orleans.
Amazing cocktails! Ask for Josephine! She's the best

Was walking around and saw the Cuban flag, being from Puerto Rico I had to stop. Staff was great, thank you Josephine for your service and attention, food was great and the drinks, well no need to ask. Great place.
Best craft cocktails ever!
Service was too notch! First time having authentic Cuban food, and it was outstanding! Will definitely be coming back when we visit again. Loved the atmosphere.
Small place, but some additional seating upstairs.  Great Cuban food and drinks.  Great service.
This a nice little place for great drinks and great food. Very friendly and quick service. Highly recommend this place to everyone
Cozy little place with Great food and fantastic blended drinks. Must try the Guava Daiquiri.
Best Cuban in the quarter.
The best drinks and food here!
The ropa vieja was good a little different than our Cuban traditional. The drink Hotel Nacional was amazing and the service was great.
Best blended cocktails in town and an amazing cuban sandwich
Good food
Best Cuban sandwich ever. Also the guava daiquiri is awesome. But that's just like my opinion man😉
great service and the atmosphere is amazing! transports you back to Cuba and fantastic cocktails

A great place to get a frozen cocktail for grownups! These creations are exceptionally delicious, nothing like the sugary sweet weak daquiris on bourbon street. Come here for genuine Cuban snacks - outstanding ceviche on plaintain chips - and a relaxing refreshment. Service was top notch genuine and friendly.
The waitress was very sweet and nice But, I have to say it wasn't authentic Cuban food.
Best bar that has ever existed

This place is great! Seriously! I've had a lot of Cuban sandwiches in my time and this ranks among the highest. My girlfriend had the arepas and they were just as praiseworthy. Only a few things on the menu but those few things are absolutely worth a try.  Also, great cocktails. My mojito was great.  Great service and a friendly staff.
Really small place including the menu Cuban food I will give 7 out of 10 and plenty of drinks
Don't miss this place!

Whenever we go here, we are super impressed.   The spot is small, not gonna lie, but what you get quality-wise is amazing.  Andrea will create whatever you order from the drink menu (get s frozen drink) or even better, tell her what you like and POOF, something amazing is before you and you can't believe it.
Delicious
Great cocktails!!!
Awful food no seasoning overpriced for under cooked rice my chicken was allllll fat lol never going back to this place I would’ve rated 0 stars if I could
So cute! Tiny but service and food were excellent. So were drinks!

There's a Cuban restaurant, two blocks down from the Acme Oyster House, which puts this place to shame (Yucca alone, which isn't on Manolito's menu, actually not much is). Try the Cuban combination at Country Flame; you won't be disappointed. Now, Mano's is mostly a bar. Its  Cuban sandwich, mediocre. Better to drive to the state Capitol, and buy one off the Caribbean food truck. No air, warm water, a couple of small, oscillating fans, and wait staff that don't mind bumping into your chair, cramped quarters, Ambiance,  not much. Skip it.
Great apps and drinks.
Small space, but hot dang the daiquiris are on point. Do yourself a favor and get the fried chick peas.
Cuban fare in a bar environment. Don't expect anything else and you won't be displeased. The ropa vieja for 2 was excellent!
(Translated by Google) Very good  (Original) Muy bueno
This place was unreal... delicious food, amazing cocktails, and wonderful service, all at a reasonable price. Wish I could come every day

Love Manolito! Staff are all fantastic...Andrea, Rachel, Konrad & Josephine,  all friendly & great to hang out at the bar with. We tried most of the drink menu - we each had our favorite (great mojitos!) but overall they were amazing. Food was great, loved the Cubanos.
This is hands down our favorite place in New Orleans.  From the amazing staff to the cocktails to the food, you absolutely owe it to yourself to visit and see for yourself.  Our home away from home.
Is a prefect Cuban place in the New Orleans city..... I am Cuban 100% recommended
Laid back, fantastic cocktails
I love everything about Manolito. Especially the black bean soup.
Best frozen daiquiri I've ever had. The mojito is also refreshing and delicious.
Best cuban sandwich!
Fantastic mojitos and AMAZING staff!! Absolutely love this place and will business every night I'm here.
BEST cocktails I’ve ever had!!

LOVE this place! The mixologists are supremely talented, try the el Presidente'.  Delicious and authentic Cuban food right in the French Quarter.  Favorite stop for before dinner cocktails or a delightful lunch.

The place doesn't look like much from the outside, but the inside is historic.. really beautiful!! The reason for the 3 stars is the cost and quantity (not quality) of the food and drinks. For 3 little cheese and ham filled fried things with a green sauce to dip them in, the cheese and ham things literally had no flavor, the only flavor was from the green sauce and it was okay, but I would've rather not eaten it... and a really thin Cuban sandwich which was very flavorful and really really good, 2 drinks in glasses that measure about 2 inches across by about 4.75 inches tall (one tea with no refills and half of it was ice...and one beer-refills not expected) it was literally not enough food for one person... Our bill was $29.70 (and that was without a tip!!) The waitress was really friendly and engaging... But I still can get over how much we paid for such little food!!
Good ole time.
Small, but intimate. Great Drinks and food
this is a GREAT place... service, drinks and food was AWESOME....
The best staff in the world. Amazing food and even better drinks.  I will go out of my way to eat at this restaurant.
Awesome food and drinks! You want to eat here!

As far as "hole in the wall" restaurants go - this one is great. Great Cuban food, great drinks, excellent service and clean restrooms. If you are looking for a spot to grab a quick lunch, this is a great option.
Awesome little spot
Excellent drinks and terrific staff.
Good food, great booze.
Great atmosphere! Drinks are spot on.
Enjoyed my meal and the staff was phenomenal!
Great arepas, cocktails, and fried chickpeas.
Wow. This a is fantastic place. Quaint and casual with great drinks.
Perfect. We were looking for something light but tasty and this fit all of requirements.
Small venue, large flavors! Truly impressed with the service, food and drinks!
Delicious food! Seriously everything was great and the cocktails were perfect
Super cozy. The food is excellent. Make sure to try a  cafecito.
Very hidden, if you stumble upon this place STOP IN!!! AMAZING!!
Great for dates and a cozy lunch.

Advertised a ropa vieja dish as a portion for two, but the portion would be considered almost adequate for one in any Cuban restaurant not in the French Quarter. Not worth the $16 plus tip. Not by a long shot. It'd be one thing if the ropa was amazing but it was decent at best.  Definitely won't be going back for a repeat.
Very nice atmosphere, nice server, and the ropa vieja was awesome!
We stopped here by chance because my husband was ravenous and the food was amazing
It’s amazing place!! My favorite spot!!!
Amazing cocktails, exceptional staff, and singular ambiance. A go-to in the quarter for us.
This is a true gem!  Tucked away in a quaint and comfortable setting the food is inspired and cocktails a delight.
What a GREAT little place for local flavor! Incredible staff and great service! tight little menu with tons of character....congrats on being recognized for it all!
Excellent place for a cocktail in this cozy little nook. A twist on a few classics with many traditional cocktails utilizing the well curated rum collection.
Cozy space. Very relaxed atmosphere. I can't eat enough of the Cuban sandwiches.
Sweet out of the way spot.  Amazing drinks, thanks to the amazing bartender. Very attentive and friendly staff. You must go!
Fabulous food and service!  Love the atmosphere, and our drinks were incredible!
Quality Cuban food and quality Cuban/Caribean feel.. cocktails 🔥🔥🔥
One of the best bars in the Quarter. Intimate place with Cuban inspired food and drinks. One of the rare places that know how to make a good frozen drink.
Incredible services, craftsmanship and a real Cuban flair/environment in the Nola area!!!

Manolito is a hidden gem in the French Quarter. Ambiance is on point. Fantastic service and the food! Hands down the best Cuban sandwich I've ever had. The beans and rice we're close to Grandma's. The Mojito and the Jazz Daiquiri were each delicious. And that flan was fantastic. Highly recommend Manolito's!
Some of the best croquetas I've ever had. Great drinks. Wonderful staff. The most great stuff per square foot anywhere in the quarter. :)

The food is excellent and the staff very pleasant. However, there is a problem, at least this night , with work flow. My entree came without the side dish I ordered and was told it would be out in a few minutes. It arrived but my wife's meal still hadn't come. I was told it takes longer to prepare. I said I prefer to dine with my wife and sent my meal back to be kept warm. Our meals came back about 5 minutes later. This means my wife's meal would have come out 10 minutes late if I hadn't sent mine back. Though it all, the server was very nice and courteous. We have eaten there several times and will continue to do so.

This tiny little Cuban masterpiece is so infinitely wonderful. Serving Cuban classics made with quality and a Cuban inspired cocktail list to rival the best the city has to offer. Its also quite a romantic spot but can get a little too loud when it gets busy. Shhhh... Keep it a locals secret please.

Had a cup of the black bean soup and a bite of the cuban sandwich: fantastic flavors in both! I wish I had ordered more food (both because of how tasty things were and because the soup was a pretty small portion). Cozy, unique atmosphere! I would like to visit again next time I'm in town.
Best drinks and amazing staff. Should have spent the whe day there. Worth every penny.

Awesome atmosphere very inviting and the drinks are amazing Tell Konrad Invee sent you

All the food here is excellent.  Some drinks are pricey, so watch what you order, but you will not be disappointed.  Everything is executed with consistency so far, after our third visit.  An excellent new establishment in the quarter.
Very delicious food and cocktails.
Great staff but the drinks very bad
Excellent cocktails and friendly service in a truly unique spot.
Delicious, very fresh ingredients and charming restaurant; my waitress was fantastic!
The ropa vieja arepas and the black bean soup, some of the best food we've had on this trip to New Orleans.

Intimate little place. At the time we visited we really had to search to find it. The staff is great. The bar program is very good. Our small plates were likewise a pleasure. They have made the most of a small space. The wife and I will be back.
Havana? New Orleans? Where are we? Sublime cuban cocktails in a shoebox of a location.
Drinks are all hand made in front of you and delicious.  Maybe the best cuban sandwich in town.
Great little spot with great people. Cubano and croquetas were delicious.

Phenomenal food and drink. Pitch-perfect ambience. Service team is effective even such a small place (and during Tales of the Cocktail, no less). Their method of order taking is a great innovation for small bars. Drinks are authentic and so is food!
Might be my new favorite date spot.
Excellent cocktails, wonderful service, well priced.  Great spot.
Fantastic strawberry daiquiri and arepas.
What alchemy is this? Amazing.
Great drink menu, great food menu. Just remember to be patient. There's only one bartender so don't expect a magic drink that shows up before you order it.

This is a very tiny place but one that prides itself in personal touch with all who enter.  The staff is very nice and engaging.  The drinks and food are done with patience, care, and gratitude.  The special attention to details in this place make it the perfect whole in the wall romantic spot to take someone while on a date.  It will throw them off guard and they probably won't know about it.  Try one of the specialty cocktails and some of the food, you will not be disappointed.  This is also a good spot for international travelers, you will have found a hidden gem worth finding.
Small spot, cool for tapas and cocktails.
Fantastic staff, service, food & beverages. A French Quarter favorite!

Great Cuban food in New Orleans. Tiny place, but very cool. Portions aren’t huge, and prices are a little high, but same as everywhere else in the area. Food was amazing and drinks were great too. Service was outstanding and super nice.
Killer lunch spot featuring beautiful cocktails and authentic Cuban food.
Killer drinks, vibes and hospitality. Great spot!
Cubano...daiquiri...nuff said...

Great drinks (although not cheap) and excited to try the food. It's a cozy space, so it can get loud if crowded, but the vibe is friendly and relaxed. Also our server was extremely friendly and accommodating. It's nice to see a whole operation running so smoothly on the first day of business.
